 comes from a video game called Portal 2.

3
00:00:06,310 --> 00:00:09,550
 In lots of video games, you use a control stick to control the camera in

4
00:00:09,550 --> 00:00:11,960
 game, but different people have different preferences for

5
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:13,630
 how the camera should behave.

6
00:00:13,630 --> 00:00:15,950
 Some feel if you press up, you should look up.

7
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:18,665
 Others like myself, feel if you press down you should look up,

8
00:00:18,665 --> 00:00:21,370
 more like you're controlling an airplane with a joystick.

9
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:24,060
 In most games you have to set this manually by going to options,

10
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:26,100
 selecting camera controls, and enabling or

11
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:29,680
 disabling a y axis and it's just a chore.

12
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:32,768
 But in portal two, watch what happens.

13
